entries.femaleVariant: Club's closed.
What're you starin' at? Got somethin' to say, say it.
What happened to Evelyn Parker?
You and Judy – what'd you argue about?
Know what happened to Evelyn Parker?
How's business?
Uh, heated exchange there with Judy. What was that all about?
Guessin' the club brings in a lot of biz?
Moxes help working girls?
Heard you give the workin' girls a helpin' hand.
Pisses its share o' costs, too. Why, lookin' to invest?
How's this any of your business?
Why you askin' me? Ya talked to Judy about her already.
That's ancient history, and like all history, it was pretty damn bloody…
Don't you have somewhere to be?
Sure, but you're the boss. Might know something more…
Evelyn jumped the Mox ship a long time ago.
And anyone not a Mox is not my damn problem.
Gonna follow-up with your own sermon on responsibility for others? Go on, your high horse is waitin'.
I'm just curious.
One thing I know about curiosity – won't get you shit 'less you got the fists and the ass to back it up.
No, just admiring your operation.
We took over this place way back when. Every day I wake up and wonder how it's still standing…
We get by, that's all I'll say.
What was it... somethin' about a riot? Joygirl murdered by a Tyger Claw?
Not the first. Just the one that tipped the scales. Folk went ballistic.
Streets overflowed with raised fists – girls, pimps, outcasts – the whole freakshow.
It's how the Mox got started. But that's old news. We're runnin' a business now, not a charity.
Can't help everyone in this city – gotta take care of our own. Moxes come first.
I said somethin'. Expect an answer.
Cat got your tongue?
Startin' to think you're a real pain in the ass.
Wanted to ask you something.
Not now.
Got a minute to talk?
Later, maybe.
Wanted to ask you something. It'll only take a sec.
Not now. Later, OK?
